{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix off-by-one error in dlsch_scale_channel array indexing\n\n### Summary\nThere is an off-by-one error in array indexing downstream of function dlsch_scale_channel in openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/dlsch_demodulation.c. When calling dlsch_scale_channel() the behavior is not what is expected. The issue may be in dlsch_scale_channel or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\n### Changes\n- Fixed hardcoded array indexing using bit shifts (<<1) and multiplication by 2\n- Replaced with dynamic indexing using frame_parms->nb_antennas_rx or n_rx parameter\n- Added missing ARM implementation for dlsch_scale_channel function\n- Corrected similar indexing issues in dlsch_channel_level, dlsch_channel_level_TM7 and related functions\n\n### Reproduction\nThe bug manifests when running LTE UE processing with nb_antennas_rx != 2. Symptoms include:\n- Incorrect channel scaling leading to poor demodulation performance\n- Potential array out-of-bounds access when nb_antennas_rx > 2\n- Segfaults in extreme cases with certain antenna configurations\n- Mismatched log2_maxh calculations causing incorrect LLR scaling\n\nTo reproduce, configure UE with 1 or 4 receive antennas and process PDSCH with TM3/4 transmission modes.\n\n"
}